{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T04:06:49.786Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Confusion Matrix"},{"type":"text","text":" is a fundamental "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"performance visualization tool"},{"type":"text","text":" for classification models that compares actual values with predicted values to show exactly where the model is getting things right or wrong — it breaks down predictions into four categories (TP, TN, FP, FN) to provide granular insight into model strengths and blind spots beyond just an accuracy score."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A confusion matrix is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"table that summarizes model performance"},{"type":"text","text":" by comparing actual labels with predicted labels:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Purpose"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Evaluates classification model performance\n- Reveals "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"where the model is confusing"},{"type":"text","text":" classes (e.g., mistaking real emails for spam)\n- Shows not just "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"how often"},{"type":"text","text":" model is correct, but "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"where"},{"type":"text","text":" it makes mistakes"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": The term \"confusion\" comes from how the matrix reveals what the model is confusing."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Four Key Values (Binary Classification)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For "},{"type":